rface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:119:| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T054258Zb_1776371017.log:48:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_result\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-04-16T20:24:39.142Z\\\",\\\"tool_id\\\":\\\"run_shell_command_1776371042532_0\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"success\\\",\\\"output\\\":\\\"/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.11/site-packages/pytest_asyncio/plugin.py:252: PytestDeprecationWarning: The configuration option \\\\\\\"asyncio_default_fixture_loop_scope\\\\\\\" is unset.\\\\nThe event loop scope for asynchronous fixtures will default to the fixture caching scope. Future versions of pytest-asyncio will default the loop scope for asynchronous fixtures to function scope. Set the default fixture loop scope explicitly in order to avoid unexpected behavior in the future. Valid fixture loop scopes are: \\\\\\\"function\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"class\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"module\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"package\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"session\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n  warnings.warn(PytestDeprecationWarning(_DEFAULT_FIXTURE_LOOP_SCOPE_UNSET))\\\\n============================= test session starts ==============================\\\\nplatform darwin -- Python 3.11.7, pytest-8.3.5, pluggy-1.5.0\\\\nsensitiveurl: .*\\\\nrootdir: /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\nconfigfile: pyproject.toml\\\\nplugins: anyio-4.12.1, respx-0.22.0, cov-5.0.0, timeout-2.2.0, asyncio-1.2.0,